A video of the "scuffle" between two security officers a father and his child in Chaka's Rock has gone viral. DURBAN - Two peace officers involved in the alleged manhandling of a child in KwaZulu-Natal's Shaka's Rock have been cleared of wrongdoing. A video of the Sunday incident has gone viral. The officers appear to drag a child from his father. READ: KwaDukuza Municipality conducts probe into 'scuffle'with child But an internal investigation by the KwaDukuza Municipality has found that the child was handled in terms of the Children's Act. The officers were taking the child to safety after his father had been arrested. Several people were arrested for contravening lockdown regulations. KwaZulu-Natal premier Sihle Zikalala has also asked for an investigation into the matter.